Iberdrola to Seek Shareholder Approval in May to Buy out Renovable Unit

-- B y   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 
2011-04-13T06:01:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/iberdrola-to-seek-shareholder-approval-in-may-to-buy-out-renovable-unit.html
Iberdrola SA (IBE)  said it will seek
approval from its shareholders to buy out its Iberdrola
Renovable unit.  Bilbao-based Iberdrola will seek approval from investors at
the general shareholder meeting scheduled for May 27, the
company said in a regulatory filing last night. The company also
will propose a dividend in cash or stocks of at least 32.6 euro
cents ($47.2) per share.  The company will pay 5 euros per 1,000 shares to investors
attending the meeting, the statement said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Esteban Duarte in Madrid at 
